properties.sfomuseum:description: Postcard set issued by Malév Hungarian Airlines, consisting of 12 postcards housed in envelope; illustrated views of aircraft fleet.a. Envelope with blue servicemark at lower left, containing b-m.b. Ilyushin Il-18 (1960-).c. Lissonov Li-2 (1946-1963).d. Aladar Zselyi’s monoplane (1912).e. Tupolev Tu-154 (1973-).f. Tupolev Tu-134 (1969-).g. Ilyushin Il-14 (1957-1968).h. Polikarpov Po-2 (1946-1956).i. Janos Adorjan’s “Libelle” (above) and Bela Takacs’ monoplane (1909).j. Monoplanes of Sandor Svachulay: “Kolibri” and “Albatrosz” (1912).k. Antal Banhidi’s touring plane “Gerle 13” (1933).l. Gyorgy Endresz’s transatlantic plane “Justice for Hungary” (1931).m. Arpad Lampich’s touring plane “Roma” (1930).
